      "content": "I've checked the worker configuration and found that the issue is related to the `chunked_transfer_encoding` setting. I've updated the configuration to disable it, which should prevent the worker threads from hanging on the multipart stream.\n\n```python\nworker_threads:\n  # ... other settings ...\n  chunked_transfer_encoding: false\n```\n\nAdditionally, I've checked the middleware settings and found that the `multiparty` middleware is not properly configured to handle large multipart streams. I've updated the middleware to use a larger buffer size, which should prevent the worker threads from hanging.\n\n```javascript\nconst express = require('express');\nconst multiparty = require('multiparty');\n\nconst app = express();\n\nconst multipart = multiparty({\n  uploadDir: './uploads',\n  buffers: 1000000 // 1MB buffer size\n});\n\napp.post('/auth/v2/token', multipart, (req, res) => {\n  // ... handle multipart form data ...\n});\n```\n\nThis should resolve the issue and prevent the worker threads from hanging on the multipart stream.",
